prompt:
What PHP code can be used to extract the energy consumption and environmental impact data of various computer network architectures outlined in the JSON data provided? How can this data be used to assess the sustainability and corporate social responsibility of organizations using these network architectures? Additionally, what measures can be taken to address any ethical implications, such as privacy concerns and potential biases in data transmission? Lastly, how might the integration of AI and IoT technologies impact the evolution of these network architectures in terms of functionality, scalability, reliability, and security measures? 
Here is the PHP code that can be used to extract the energy consumption and environmental impact data from the JSON data:
$json = '{
    "networks": [
        {
            "name": "Ethernet",
            "energy_consumption": "high",
            "environmental_impact": "high",
            "privacy_concerns": "low",
            "potential_biases": "low",
            "functionality": "limited",
            "scalability": "high",
            "reliability": "high",
            "security_measures": "moderate"
        },
        {
            "name": "Wireless",
            "energy_consumption": "medium",
            "environmental_impact": "medium",
            "privacy_concerns": "moderate",
            "potential_biases": "moderate",
            "functionality": "moderate",
            "scalability": "moderate",
            "reliability": "medium",
            "security_measures": "moderate"
        },
        {
            "name": "Fiber Optic",
            "energy_consumption": "low",
            "environmental_impact": "low",
            "privacy_concerns": "high",
            "potential_biases": "low",
            "functionality": "high",
            "scalability": "high",
            "reliability": "high",
            "security_measures": "high"
        },
        {
            "name": "Satellite",
            "energy_consumption": "high",
            "environmental_impact": "low",
            "privacy_concerns": "high",
            "potential_biases": "moderate",
            "functionality": "limited",
            "scalability": "low",
            "reliability": "low",
            "security_measures": "low"
        }
    ]
}';
$data = json_decode($json);
foreach($data->networks as $network){
  echo "Network Name: " . $network->name . "<br>";
  echo "Energy Consumption: " . $network->energy_consumption . "<br>";
  echo "Environmental Impact: " . $network->environmental_impact . "<br><br>";
}
This code will loop through each network in the JSON data and print out the network name, energy consumption, and environmental impact.
